nturies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aConstitutional historyzFrance. 0aRepresentative government and representation. 4aConstant, Benjamin. 4aFrankreich / Geschichte. 4aFrankreich / Literaturgeschichte. 4aFrankreich / Politische Theorie. 4aPolitische Philosophie. 4aPublizistik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aConstant, Benjamin.  aFrance/History of Literature.  aFrance/History.  aFrance/Political Theory.  aJournalism.  aPhilosophy of Politics.1 aAzorin, Lisa.1 aDelbouille, Paul.1 aHofmann, Etienne.1 aKloocke, Kurt.1 aPaoletti, Giovanni.1 aRosset, François, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWilfinger, Laura.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC0 cprintz978311023446640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311023447340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110234473423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110234473/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014